<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EC) No 1477/97 of 28 July 1997 on transitional measures concerning the application of quotas of fresh tomatoes intended for processing for the 1996/97 marketing year </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1477/97 1996/97. turustusaastal t&ouml;&ouml;tlemiseks etten&auml;htud v&auml;rskete tomatite kvootide kohaldamist k&auml;sitlevate &uuml;leminekumeetmete kohta 28. juuli 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 2201/96 of 28 October 1996 on the common organisation of the markets in processed fruit and vegetable products (1), and in particular Article 26 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 28. oktoobri 1996. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2201/96 puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljatooteturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) eriti selle artiklit 26, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the quantities of fresh tomatoes which qualify for production aid in the 1996/97 marketing year are fixed in Regulation (EEC) No 668/93 on the introduction of a limit to the granting of production aid for processed tomato products (2); whereas, in that marketing year, production exceeded those quantities in certain Member States and in certain groups of products, while remaining lower than those quantities for another group; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: 1996/97. turustusaastal tootmistoetuse saamise tingimustele vastavate v&auml;rskete tomatite kogused m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindaks m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 668/93 t&ouml;&ouml;deldud tomatisaaduste puhul tootmistoetuse piiramise kohta; (2) k&otilde;nealusel turustusaastal &uuml;letas tootmine teatavates liikmesriikides ja teatavate tooter&uuml;hmade puhul nimetatud kogused, j&auml;&auml;des teiste r&uuml;hmade puhul nendest kogustest madalamaks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, under the new common organisation of the market adopted by Regulation (EC) No 2201/96, quotas are fixed for those products for the grant of production aid applicable from the 1997/98 harvest, adapting them to the economic development of the market for each product; whereas, as a result, in some cases the quota has been increased in relation to that for the preceding marketing year; whereas it is necessary to take account of this new orientation to facilitate the transition from the old arrangements to the new ones by providing for the transfer, for the 1996/97 marketing year, of the remaining quantities for a given group of products to those groups which exceeded the quotas, within the quota limit laid down for each group and Member State referred to in Annex III to Regulation (EC) No 2201/96; </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 2201/96 vastuv&otilde;etud uue &uuml;hise turukorralduse alusel m&auml;&auml;ratakse nende toodete puhul kvoodid tootmistoetuse andmiseks 1997/98. aasta saagist alates, kohandades neid iga toote turu majandusarengut silmas pidades; selle tulemusel on m&otilde;nel juhul kvooti eelmise turustusaastaga v&otilde;rreldes suurendatud; vanalt korralt uuele &uuml;lemineku h&otilde;lbustamiseks tuleks 1996/97. turustusaastaks s&auml;testada teatavate tooter&uuml;hmade kasutamata koguste &uuml;leviimine kvooti &uuml;letanud tooter&uuml;hmadele, v&otilde;ttes siiski arvesse igale tooter&uuml;hmale ja igale liikmesriigile m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2201/96 III lisas kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud kvoote; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to qualify for production aid, processing enterprises must provide proof to the satisfaction of the competent authorities in the Member States that a price at least equal to the minimum price has been paid to the producers; </inglise>
<eesti> tootmistoetuse saamiseks peavad t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;tted esitama liikmesriigi p&auml;devatele asutustele piisavad t&otilde;endid selle kohta, et tootjatele on makstud miinimumhinnaga v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;rdne hind; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to Commission Regulations (EEC) Nos 1558/91 (3) and 1794/93 (4), the Member States have notified the Commission of the quantities for which aid applications have been made as well as the total quantities of tomatoes processed in the 1996/97 marketing year; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruste (EM&Uuml;) nr 1558/91 (3) ja (EM&Uuml;) nr 1794/93 (4) alusel on liikmesriigid teatanud komisjonile kogused, mille osas on esitatud toetuse taotlused, ning 1996/97. turustusaastal t&ouml;&ouml;deldud tomatite &uuml;ldkogused; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Products Processed from Fruit and Vegetables, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las puu- ja k&ouml;&ouml;giviljatooteturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to facilitate the transition from the arrangements provided for in Regulation (EEC) No 668/93 to the arrangements provided for in Regulation (EC) No 2201/96, production aid granted for processed tomato products shall be limited, for the 1996/97 marketing year, to the quantities of processed products obtained from the following quantities, in tonnes of fresh tomatoes: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 668/93 s&auml;testatud korralt m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 2201/96 s&auml;testatud korrale &uuml;lemineku h&otilde;lbustamiseks tuleks tomatitoodete puhul antavat tootmistoetust piirata 1996/97. turustusaastal nende toodete kogustega, mis on saadud j&auml;rgmistest v&auml;rskete tomatite tonnides v&auml;ljendatud kogustest: </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall distribute, by product group, the quantities in addition to the quantities for which applications for production aid have already been made and notified to the Commission pursuant to Article 18 (a) of Regulation (EEC) No 1558/91 proportionally to the processing undertakings on the basis of the quantities declared by those undertakings under Article 8 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1794/93 for which the minimum price has been paid to the producers. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid jaotavad kogused, mis on saadud t&auml;iendavalt juba esitatud tootmistoetuste taotluste kogustele ja millest on komisjoni vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1558/91 artikli 18 punktile a teavitatud, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemisettev&otilde;tete vahel v&otilde;rdeliselt tooter&uuml;hmade kaupa, v&otilde;ttes aluseks nimetatud ettev&otilde;tete poolt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1794/93 artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel deklareeritud kogused, mille eest on miinimumhind tootjatele makstud. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall take all the necessary measures to ensure that the overall quantity per Member State provided for in Article 1 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 668/93 is not exceeded. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed tagamaks, et liikmesriigi kohta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 668/93 artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud &uuml;ldkogust ei &uuml;letata. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> In order to be eligible for production aid in respect of the additional quantities, processors must submit a supplementary application within 30 days of the entry into force of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> T&auml;iendavate koguste puhul peavad t&ouml;&ouml;tlejad tootmistoetuse tingimustele vastamiseks 30 p&auml;eva jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse j&otilde;ustumist esitama t&auml;iendava taotluse. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Those applications shall comprise: </inglise>
<eesti> Taotlustes on: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the name and address of the applicant; </inglise>
<eesti> a) taotleja nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the name and address of the producer; </inglise>
<eesti> b) tootja nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the net weight of the raw materials declared under Article 8 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1794/93 for which a minimum price has been paid to the producers; </inglise>
<eesti> c) m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1794/93 artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel deklareeritud tooraine netomass, mille eest on miinimumhind tootjatele makstud; </eesti>
<inglise> (d) the net weight of the finished products obtained from the raw materials referred to under (c). </inglise>
<eesti> d) punktis c osutatud toorainest saadud valmistoodete netomass. </eesti>
<inglise> These finished products shall be broken down according to the rate of aid for which they are eligible; </inglise>
<eesti> Need valmistooted liigitatakse selle toetuse m&auml;&auml;ra alusel, mille tingimustele nad vastavad; </eesti>
<inglise> (e) proof, to the satisfaction of the Member State, that they have paid the producers a price at least equal to the minimum price for the quantities referred to under (c); </inglise>
<eesti> e) liikmesriigi jaoks piisavad t&otilde;endid selle kohta, et nad on tootjatele punktis c osutatud koguste eest maksnud miinimumhinnaga v&auml;hemalt v&otilde;rdse hinna; </eesti>
<inglise> (f) a declaration by the processor that the finished products comply with Community quality standards. </inglise>
<eesti> f) t&ouml;&ouml;tleja kinnitus selle kohta, et valmistooted vastavad &uuml;henduse kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
